12.ABOUT:
UFS Explorer Professional Recovery is an all-in-one data recovery program for highly-challenging data loss cases. It is primarily dedicated to assisting data recovery professionals and technicians in restoring photos, videos, documents and other types of files that were lost or deleted from all sorts of storages, including simple, complex and defective. This software supports a wide range of Windows, Linux, macOS and BSD file systems, as well as various storage technologies, including Windows D.namic Disks, Storage Spaces and deduplication, Linux mdadm and LVM with Thin Provisioning, and Apple Software RAID, Core Storage and Time Machine. Moreover, it allows decrypting volumes encrypted with BitLocker, FileVault 2, LUKS and APFS directly in its interface, skipping the step of volume unlocking in the operating system. 

Other useful features of UFS Explorer Professional Recovery are the following:

Support of numerous RAID configurations (standard, nested, custom and vendor-specific variations such as Drobo BeyondRAID, Synology Hybrid RAID, Btrfs-RAID and ZFS RAID-Z);
Compatibility with such modern virtualization technologies as VMware, Hyper-V, VirtualBox, QEMU and XEN;
Working with MRT Data Explorer (including with task files generated with this software and defects maps associated with them), as well as with drives connected to DeepSpar Disk Imager via LAN without any third-party solutions;
Multiple settings to configure the procedure of storage accessing and opening;
Numerous storage scan-related settings: several options for existing file systems processing, possibility to pause the on-going scanning procedure and save its intermediate results, etc.;
Automatic detection of lost partitions, partitions auto-aligning, auto-span tool and possibility to define partitions manually;
In-built disk imager provided with functions for optional damaged blocks omission and defective areas maps generations;
Low-level data analysis instruments: hexadecimal viewer and editor, data interpreter, parity calculator, parallel search, etc.

There are UFS Explorer Professional Recovery Windows, macOS and Linux versions. Any of them can be downloaded and installed absolutely for free and used for evaluation and trial purposes. In addition, with the trial version of the software it is possible to recover an unlimited number of files up to 768 KB each.
